cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with load balancing in a network of caching servers. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper considers communication cost and proximity in the server redirection process. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a load balancing scheme that considers multiple constraints and aims to optimize performance. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses the power of two choices approach and proposes a new randomized load balancing scheme. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper aims to improve load balancing performance while considering storage and communication constraints.
